,"Sperm reaches cervical mucus within 90 seconds","The cervix stores viable sperm for 2 weeks","The typical ejaculate contains 40-600 million sperm"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EA normal ejaculate typically contains \u003Cstrong\u003E40-600 million sperm\u003C/strong\u003E per millilitre. The statement that \u003Cstrong\u003Esperm reaches cervical mucus within 90 seconds\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - it typically takes 2-10 minutes. The \u003Cstrong\u003Ecervix stores viable sperm for 2 weeks\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - sperm remains viable in the cervical crypts for 3-5 days. \u003Cstrong\u003ESperm motility peaks at 24 hours\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - sperm motility is highest immediately after ejaculation and gradually declines. The statement that \u003Cstrong\u003Emost sperm reach the fallopian tubes within 30 minutes\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - only a small fraction of sperm reach the fallopian tubes, taking several hours.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Sperm typically takes 2-10 minutes to reach cervical mucus after ejaculation","The cervix can store viable sperm for up to 3-5 days","Normal ejaculate contains 40-600 million sperm per millilitre"],"references":["Dcunha R, Hussein RS, Ananda H, Kumari S, Adiga SK, Kannan N, Zhao Y, Kalthur G. Current Insights and Latest Updates in Sperm Motility and Associated Applications in Assisted Reproduction. Reprod Sci. 2022 Jan;29(1):7-25. doi: 10.1007/s43032-020-00408-y. Epub 2020 Dec 7. PMID: 33289064; PMCID: PMC7721202.","Gurung P, Yetiskul E, Jialal I. Physiology, Male Reproductive System. [Updated 2023 May 1]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538429/","Orsolini MF, Meyers SA, Dini P. An Update on Semen Physiology, Technologies, and Selection Techniques for the Advancement of In Vitro Equine Embryo Productio